    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready, skim through these steps then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary, and if you like your steak well-done, it may take you a little longer than 10 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-and-chive-pork-steak-with-crushed-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat and boil half a kettle</p><p>Pat your <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and rub them with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> seasoned steak </strong>and cook on one side for 3 min or until browned</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-and-chive-pork-steak-with-crushed-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 4-8 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-and-chive-pork-steak-with-crushed-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>leek[s]</strong> into chunky rounds</p><p>Wash to remove any grit from between the leaves</p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-and-chive-pork-steak-with-crushed-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork steak<strong> </strong>is browned on one side, reduce the heat to medium-high, flip and cook 1 min further</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[255ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> stock</strong> and <strong>sliced leeks</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 4 min or until the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-and-chive-pork-steak-with-crushed-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, add a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>roughly crush with a fork \u2013 these are your <strong>crushed potatoes</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-and-chive-pork-steak-with-crushed-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork steak<strong> </strong>is cooked through, add your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!),<strong> </strong>your<strong> soft cheese </strong>and the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>chives </strong>and cook, uncovered, for 1 min<strong> </strong>further<strong> </strong>or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy mustard & chive pork steak</strong></p><p>Season generously with <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-and-chive-pork-steak-with-crushed-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy mustard & chive pork steak</strong> with the <strong>crushed potatoes </strong>and<strong> salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon over any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>mustard & chive</strong> <strong>sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
